race.comment: TORVEGA (12) has been unlucky not to have broken through last preparation and just missed at Kilmore first up from the front. He draws inside today and has more to give. Fitter again and shapes as the one to beat. PRINCE OF BROOKY (6) was tipped out after a solid effort at Ballarat on debut and just missed resuming at Geelong when expected to need it. Has an awkward barrier and she can feature with the extra fitness. BLACK EYED BLONDE (8) just missed as favourite at Sale first-up and then didn't have the best of it at Ballarat well supported again. Missed a whisker here before the break and will get every chance from the inside barrier. PRESSCODE (5) showed enough as favourite at Morphettville on debut to consider.
